Program: Discovery
Title: Galaxies
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrykt
Last Broadcast Date: 10 December 2003
Change, drama, evolution and surprise in the galaxy strewn cosmos. Our own galaxy with 100 billion stars, the Milky Way, is just one of billions of galaxies in the universe. Our exploration of space is only just beginning. Far from static galaxies are constantly moving and could even collide with one another. Show less